HEADWORD: Hyphomycetes
<hw>Hy`pho*my*ce"tes</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos> <ety>[NL.,
fr. Gr. <?/ a web + <?/, <?/, a mushroom.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld>
<def>One of the great division of fungi, containing those species which
have naked spores borne on free or only fasciculate threads.</def>
